## full() function

from https://github.com/CesiumGS/cesium/blob/master/Source/Core/defined.js

**Signature:**

```typescript
export declare function full<T>(val: T): val is Exclude<T, null | undefined>;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  val | T | The object. |

**Returns:**

val is Exclude&lt;T, null \| undefined&gt;

Returns true if the object is defined and not empty string, returns false otherwise.

## Example


```javascript
full('foo') // true
full('') // false
full(undefined) // false
full(0) // true
```
